    public class DefaultVisualLocationBuffer6
extends AbstractPMActivationBuffer6
implements IVisualLocationBuffer, ICompilableBuffer
    since visual-location and visual buffers share the same state information (stored in the visual buffer) so care must be taken to use the visual buffers state information and not visual location's

      • checkForBufferStuff

        public void checkForBufferStuff()
        we stuff the buffer if this buffer is empty and free AND the visual buffer is free. If they are, we create a basic visual search request, set the state (ours, not the visual buffers) to unrequested, and pass the request on to the visual location chunk pattern processor
